column35: General_Feedback

Nabia's conversation was fine. CH wanted to know the balance but was unable to verify the access code. Nabia assisted accordingly. However, after verifying the phone number and sending the access code via text, Nabia should have informed the customer that they will be getting the access code as a text but no such information was given to the customer. Usage of courtesy words and phrases, with an appropriate courteous tone, could and should have been ensured.
Nabia's conversation was fine. Usage of courtesy and empathy words and phrases could and should have been better. CH wanted to know about a transaction.
Nabia's conversation was fine. CH wanted to know as to why he had not been able to load more money on the card. CH also was assisted with the card status / activation of his other card.
Ben's conversation was fine. CH wanted to know the transactions on 2 of her Ready cards to understand as to why the balance on her cards was low.
Shane's conversation was fine. Long pauses and dead air must always be avoided. Card was registered for the customer for online use.
Eddie's conversation was fine. CH wanted to know the status of his cards. Long pauses and dead air must always be avoided.
Alex had a fine conversation. However, customer must not be interrupted while speaking. CH wanted to know about the declined and posted transactions.
Andrew's conversation was fine. CH wanted to know as to why the transaction declined, which was due to the required incidental hold.

Andrew's conversation was not okay. First of, just saying sorry for the sake of saying it, never works and is not helpful. Sincere courtesy, apology and empathy words and phrases should have been used in this customer interaction. Tone also could have been better. It sounded as if Andrew was annoyed at the customer because customer was asking the same thing again and again and it was also Andrew's mistake that the customer was asking the same thing over again because Andrew did not provide her with the correct answer. CH mentioned multiple times on the call that her transaction was declining with United and as per the declined records, it was due to insufficient funds. Only if Andrew would have explained this, CH would have been satisfied. But Andrew did not check the declined records and informed the customer that there was no decline, which was incorrect information. It also sounded as if Andrew was in some kind of a hurry to end the call, which also did not sound good. Card account was also not notated.

CH called to activate and transferred to CS for profile update. Mary did a great job with the welcome script. Mary had an opportunity to take ownership by verifying if work number on MCP was correct or could be removed. Mary had an opportunity to utilize the SMS alert scripting. Mary had an opportunity to prepare for the call as she was constantly yawning throughout the call. Nice personalization and CH engagement. Close call notes were fine; however Mary failed to notate CH declined email.

CH received paper-check and also has a new Direct Express card and unsure how to get the paper-check on the card.  Tyonna had an opportunity to not cut off the third party caller (permission granted by CH) as he was asking his questions.   No welcome script results in failed Policy and Procedure.  CH Profile SOP was incomplete.  This result s in second failed Policy and Procedure.  Inquiry about where he can cash the check and also use of ATM’s.  Tyonna let third party know he’d have to use a Money Pass ATM for free surcharge.  Tyonna encouraged CH to ‘google’ the Money Pass ATM’s; an opportunity to educate on CH website.  Tyonna confirmed to CH he can deposit the check at any ATM.  This is completely inaccurate; no funds can be deposited to DE cards other than SSA for monthly benefit.  This results in failed FCR for accuracy.  Tyonna had an opportunity to personalize the call and use the proper closing which requires Direct Express to be included.  Close call notes were fine.

CH sent to CS following card activation.  Ayanna did a nice job with the welcome script.  Mobile was updated and same as what was in the work field.  Ayanna had an opportunity remove the duplicate number.  Ayanna had a missed opportunity to use DCFC scripting for SMS alerts.  CH said he wanted alerts for card transactions.  Ayanna went over other alerts..  No alerts were set.  This results in failed FCR for accuracy.  A note has been sent to have these corrected.  Incomplete CH Profile SOP resulting in a failed Policy and Procedure.   Close call notes didn’t reflect content of the call.

CH called back because SSA told her we have account and routing number. Julia was not clear and easily understood when saying “I’m in Omaha NE you know we wouldn’t be mailing those all across the country.” Also Including 'they will get there when they get there' when referring to the card usage and account and routing numbers. CH had to give full card number in order for Julia to access the account, which means the call didn’t auto populate and CH should have been sent back to IVR for authentication resulting in a failure for Policy and Procedure. Julia lost control of the call when shared instructions for card to card transfer when CH just wanted to know about routing and account number. Julia provided inaccurate information when she told CH that SSA shouldn’t be sending paper checks resulting in a failed FCR for accuracy. Julia lost control of call again by discussing personal bank account and routing numbers which has nothing to do with CH issue. Julia accessed the account and did not complete CH Profile SOP resulting in a 2nd failure for Policy and Procedure. Julia did not provide proper closing “Thank you for calling Direct Express” which is required on every call. Julia did not utilize her tools and check the FCR box.

CH called to inquire about an upcoming DD. Lillie did a great job verifying that CH was set up for alerts. Lillie had nice flow and call control; AST 4:42 min.  Close call notes were fine. Great call Lillie!

CH called wanting SMS alerts setup. Lillie had an opportunity to take ownership by removing work phone number as she had verified it was her mobile. A note has  been sent to have this corrected.  Lillie did a great job setting up SMS alerts, all entered correctly. Nice helpful tone and CH engagement.  Close call notes were fine.

CH activated card and sent to CS for profile update.  Direct Express was not used in the greeting.  This is a requirement.  Andrea  did a good job reading the Welcome Script however did not notate this in the CSR comments section.  A note has been sent to have this corrected.  Andrea had an incomplete CH Profile SOP which results in a Policy and Procedure failure.  Andrea offered alerts, CH accepted, alerts were not set.  This results in a failure for FCR accuracy.  Andrea had the opportunity to show ownership and offer promotional messages.  Andrea provided the CH with misinformation regarding the Cash Access option.  There were no close call notes which results in a 2nd policy and procedure failure for Notations.

CH called to activate and transferred to CS for profile update. CH also had question regarding DD status. Tiffany did a great job with welcome script and SMS scripting. Tiffany had an opportunity to take ownership and remove work number since CH has no available phone number at the time. A note has been sent to have this corrected. Close call notes were fine; however Tiffany failed to notate CH also had DD inquiry.

CH reported card lost.  CH distraught and became increasingly more emotional.  No empathy or acknowledgment of concern.  Missed opportunity for better call control.  Tyonna missed the opportunity to probe to determine exactly what the CH was requesting. This results in a failed FCR.  Tyonna didn’t follow the Threat Mitigation process as outlined in the DCFC and questioned CH as to why/how he could verify all his information and come through with his information populated if he didn’t really have his card.  No close call notations results in a failed Policy and Procedure.  Tyonna ended up disconnecting the call while the CH was still talking. This was confirmed via an Intello Hang Up report. This results in a failed Integrity and Professionalism.

CH activated card and sent to CS for profile update. Emmaly did a good job with the Welcome script.  Emmaly had an opportunity to use please and thank you when asking/receiving information from the CH.   Emmaly verified the cell phone on file but did not verify the DOB.  This results in a failed Policy and Procedure for CH Profile SOP.  Emmaly requested an email address which the CH provided, however it was not updated and close call notes indicate the CH did not provide an email address.   The CH opted out of alerts.  This results in a failed Integrity and Professionalism for false notations.  The incorrect closing was provided.  Direct Express is required in the closing of all calls.

CH calling along with his advocate stating that he never received his card.   Denise did a good job verifying the account with the CH and then asking if it was okay to speak to his advocate on his behalf.  Denise had the opportunity to use please and thank you when requesting/receiving information from the CH.  Denise informed the CH that she could reissue the card and get it to him in 2-3 business days and advised the CH about the $13.50 fee.  Denise had the opportunity to show ownership and advise CH to allow 1 business day for printing of the card.  Denise did not use the required closing for this call.  Direct Express is required in the closing of the call.  Close call notes are fine.

CH activated card and sent to CS to have profile updated.    Brittany did a great job with the welcome script.  An opportunity to share value add for SMS alerts.  Great overall call flow and CH engagement.  Remember to notate CSR Comments section on the Card Summary page in MCP that you’ve completed the welcome script.  A note has been sent to have this added.   Brittany has an opportunity to use the proper closing by using Direct Express.  Close call notes should include CH declined SMS alerts.

CH calling to find out about DD.  Mercedes advised the CH the deposit was still pending and to check back in the morning as it had not been released yet.  The CH then asked if she could be set up with alerts to be notified of when the deposit hit the account.  Mercedes verified the phone number but failed to verify the DOB and ask for an email address.  This results in a failure of Policy and Procedure for CH Profile SOP.  There was a lot of dead air while Mercedes was setting up the alerts.  Good detailed close call notes on account.  The call was over at 3:25 but Mercedes stayed on the line until 4:05 and then disconnected the call.  This results in a failure for Integrity and Professionalism.

CH activated account and sent to CS for profile updates.  Female voice on call and referenced, ‘we just activated account and ….’  Matthew had an opportunity to confirm the person who called was the CH given the welcome script was provided to the third party who called and uncertain if on speaker or were swapping the phone.  Matthew eventually got permission from CH to speak to third party.  CH verified number on account and said it was a mobile number but third party said it wasn’t CH’s mobile.  Matthew had opportunity to confirm if this is a good contact for CH or if he had an alternate number for his profile as the same number was listed in MCP as a work number.  No SMS alerts were offered for future once CH obtains his own mobile or gave permission to send to the mobile he just confirmed or if CH obtains an email address.  Welcome script not added to CSR Comments section in Card Summary screen.  Close call notes were fine.

Non card holder calling in on account.  Latrina informed the caller she would need to speak to the CH to verify the account but she had the opportunity to use better word choices on this contact like please and thank you.  Latrina had the opportunity to use a more friendlier tone.  Latrina had the opportunity to show empathy on this contact.  Latrina was rude to the caller which results in failed Integrity and Professionalism.  No close call notes were provided which results in a failed Policy and Procedure.

CH inquired about an Uber transaction.  Matthew has an opportunity to not tell the CH her profile information but rather ask the CH to provide the information so we can confirm it against MCP.  The address isn’t part of the verification OR the CH Profile SOP, that and telling the CH only her partial address details should never take place.  Shane had the CH’s alert details available in MCP and asked her if she received her alerts.  A better approach is to review MCP alerts/notifications to make sure the status before making the assumption.  CH said she did, however, she only has two activated and one of the two is set incorrectly.  A missed opportunity to correct this for the CH.  Long dead airs should have been avoided and incorrect closing used.  Direct Express is required in all greeting and closings.  Close call notes were fine.

CH called inquiring if he had any pending deposits. MIchelle had an opportunity to say please and thank you when asking for CH's information. Michelle had an incomplete CH Profile SOP by not going over the alerts.  Michelle had an opportunity to take ownership when reviewing email and mobile phone on an account that already has it listed, have CH either give you the information or you repeat what is listed for accuracy. Michelle had an opportunity to personalize the call by using the CH's name. Close call notes were fine.

CH called for balance on lost card. Linel had an opportunity to not go through profile update on a blocked card, it can’t be updated in this status. CH wanted to wait couple of days to search for card and then call back to re-issue. Close call notes were not clear about what happened during call.

Dead airs could have been avoided. 
CH was not admin on the account and was not able to load funds on the other sup cards. 
Agent should have used the acknowledgment statement after listening to the concern instead of keeping quiet. 
Agent should have kept the CH informed what was going on. 
There was a hold for more than 2 minutes without any interaction with CH. 
Agent escalated the issue and asked to wait. 

Account was not notated.

Richard’s conversation was just okay. Usage of courtesy, apology, empathy and value added phrases should have been ensured. Richard also needs to ensure not to interrupt the customer while they are speaking but multiple verbal collisions were observed on this call from Richard’s end. CH wanted to get the balance from her card to be cashed out because she did not want to spend the funds down. Richard advised the customer that a money order will be sent to her for the balance available on the card but failed to do so. The card account is still open and active and the funds are still on the card. Moreover, Richard did not take any ownership to verify the address before issuing the money order (which was also not issued in this case). Card account was also not notated.

CH called to get help with card activation. Agent provided partial walkthrough of creating an online account for activation upto the activation link. Agent should have demonstrated the ownership of walking him through the rest of the setup process as well.

CH called to check the card balance. Agent should ask for the card number first and then  should verify the expiry date. Agent should follow the proper call flow. Agent should avoid dead air and should use acknowledgment statements.

CH called because she was having issues accessing her online account. Fernando’s tone and pace were great. The CH was instructed step by step on how to reset her password. Fernando should’ve explained the differences between the password and PIN since the CH seemed to be confused about them. Additional assistance was offered, account was notated accordingly.

CH called because she was having issues accessing her online account. Fernando’s tone and pace were great. The CH was instructed step by step on how to reset her password. Fernando should’ve explained the differences between the password and PIN since the CH seemed to be confused about them. Additional assistance was offered, account was notated accordingly.

CH wanted to know how he got the card. 
CH was asking the balance. 
Agent was attentive, CH was very clear telling the concern. 
Agent could have provided the information from the DCFC i.e. MB Financial is offering Single load corporately loaded Incentive cards to its consumers. Cards are not available to consumers for direct purchase which means that the cards cannot be signed up online. These cards will be distributed by various employers/business providers to the employees.

Caller called in about a master BBA card. Agent obtained CPF but CH was unable to understand him. Agent failed to explain that we need the ID # given by Brazilian Gov to her which is like a ssn. Agent asked for CS number and asked to call that number.

CH called to inquire if he can transfer the funds from the card. Agent provided the CH with the options. Agent should always inform the CH before placing the call on a hold. This falls under call avoidance. Ch was not informed properly before he was placed on a hold. Agent should sound helpful and friendly. Agent should use courtesy words and acknowledgment statements.

Caller was calling the wrong CS. 
Agent informed the caller that Bank is several cards. 
Caller already told that Visa provided him this number.

Agent was not ready for the greeting. 
CH wanted to know the balance on the card. 
CH already provided the concern and card number in the beginning of the call. 
Card closed due to expiry/inactivity
Agent informed the balance and status of the card. 
More call control was required in the call, as CH provided the same information before but agent asked the same again and again. 
There was another lady talking who was providing information to the caller.

Agent needs to work on active listening. CH provided the correct number but agent was unable to take it down correctly. Agent asked CH to provide the correct number. CH provided his Son's number. Agent pulled up the account of CH's son and asked him to ask his son to callback. Agent should have proactively asked the CH if he was calling about his own account or for his son's account. Agent failed to probe and provided a resolution based on an assumption that CH was calling for his Son's account.

CH called to activate her card. Amanda’s tone was good. We should never ask for the full card number or activate cards without a user ID. The explanation on how to load the card was incomplete. Additional assistance was offered, account was notated accordingly.
Agent needs to improve tone and actively listening. Agent told CH we don't have any account for him which was not true. Agent assisted CH in sign up for TVG.

I was able to pull the card account in first attempt. CH wanted to activate the card. Notations left was not concise. “Activate Card\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t““Change PIN\r\n”Card was activated and PIN was setup.
Agent needs to work on active listening. CH had to repeat the card number for the agent. Agent verified the CH. Agent activated the card for the CH.

CH called for apple pay verification. Agent misheard the CH and thought he provided the full ssn. Agent guided the CH never to provide full ssn twice which was not what happened in the call. Agent then confirmed the last few transactions and told CH that a request for linking the card with apple pay has been sent. Agent informed the CH to expect an email in 24-48 hours. The time frame is 24 hours. Agent notated the account.

Mike’s conversation was fine. CH wanted to know if she could withdraw cash from the card or not and was advised accordingly. However, Mike needs to always ensure effective listening. On this call, the customer provided the card number very clearly and multiple times but Mike did not listen effectively and that is why was able to get it on the 3rd or 4th attempt, which did not sound good. Also, the usage of empathy and courtesy words and phrases should have been much better and effective.

CH called to get a pending trans released back on the card from PAYPAL for AUD376.91. Agent advised the CH to wait until the expiry date for the trans. Agent should sound helpful and friendly and should use courtesy words and phrases and should work on effective listening. Agent should avoid talking over the CH. Agent should have followed the pre auth release process and should have requested docs from the merchant. Agent should have probed the CH properly. Appropriate wording must be used.

Agent should always acknowledge the concern before asking for phone number. 
I was able to pull the card account using the phone number in first attempt. 
Agent needs to work on his listening skills. 
Agent should always answer what was asked by the CH instead of putting another question or keep on with authentication. 
Agent was no wrong account. CH was providing all the correct information as the account. There was no email address listed in the account. 
Agent took very long time to pull the card account.
Agent could have asked the concern meanwhile. 
No FCR was provided as agent was not able to pull the card account and CH had to call back.

CH called to get information on a recent payment she made. Lucas sounded disinterested and not helpful, no acknowledgement or empathy was shown to the CH. The poor Customer service provided resulted on a request for a supervisor (which was never sent). Agent disconnected the call.
CH called to reclaim his funds. Louis’ tone and pace were great, the MO was processed as requested and all the pertinent information was relayed to the CH.
CH called to inquire if the card was active. Agent informed the CH about the status of the cards. Agent should work on effective listening. Agent should sound energetic.

Card was about to expire and CH wanted to know how he can renew it. 
Agent should have acknowledge the concern. 
Address was updated and repeated. 
Agent should have explained the CH the options to access the remaining funds or if we are going to renew the card. Agent updated the address and informed the CH that he is going to send the Money Order. 
Agent should never mimic the CH. 
Hold duration could have been reduced. 
Agent should have informed the time frame required for the Money Order.

Chris had an okay conversation. Tone sounded dull and low and should have been upbeat and lively. Customer must never be interrupted while speaking. Ownership should have been taken to properly and confidently educate the customer that an online account for Ready card cannot be created but it was never informed to the customer. Ownership should also have been taken to update the phone number / email address of the customer. Long pauses and dead air must always be avoided. CH wanted to access the online account to register the card. Card was registered.

CH called to get general information. Paulo’s tone was good. An acknowledgement statement after the CH explained her concern was not given. The CH was incorrectly advised that she would be able to withdraw $250 per week while she is travelling though London and Paris. Ending was abrupt, account was notated.

CH called to inquire why his trans was declining. Agent informed the CH that the trans was declining due to the merchant being international. Agent advised the CH to contact the merchant and speak with the about the currency conversion. Agent failed to inform the CH about the International Transactions Fee of 2.5%, this was the reason the trans was declining. Agent needs to work on effective listening and should pay attention to what the CH is asking.
CH called to inquire about the card PIN. Agent informed the CH about the PIN and how to use the card. Agent should avoid dead air and should work on effective listening.
Ch called to activate the card. Agent activated the card and set up a PIN. Agent should work on effective listening and should avoid dead air.

Richard’s conversation was just okay. Usage of courtesy, empathy, apology and value added phrases should have been ensured. Verbal collisions and speaking over the customer must always be avoided. CH was advised about the balance on the card and how to and withdraw it. When the customer mentioned that she wanted to transfer the money from her card to a bank account in Germany, Richard should have taken an ownership to let the customer know that transferring funds from card to a bank account is not an option but this was also not told to the customer.
Camila’s conversation was fine. However, she needs to ensure not to interrupt the customer while speaking. Caller was not the CH and wanted to get the card all cashed out. Camila advised accordingly.

Lucas had an okay conversation. CH lost the card and wanted a money order to be sent to him. Lucas sent the money order. Lucas informed the customer that the balance on the card was $17.34 but the CH thought that Lucas told him that the balance on the card was $70. That is why the CH asked Lucas that someone was trying to charge his card for $50 and why it did not go through as he had $70 on the card. Lucas could not understand the question of the customer and failed to answer this. The only thing Lucas was supposed to tell the customer as answer to his question was that the balance on the card was not $70 but $17.34

I was able to get the account in first attempt. 
Agent took a bit long to pull the card account. 
CH was having issues with his online account. 
Business name was provided three times in the call. 
Issue was escalated as CH was admin on the account.

column34: RPG MC 15 Mo Inc US Only
column35:
CH was trying to use the card but it was giving message that it has been expired. 
Hold was not required to check the decline. 
Pre-Auth Transaction-POS Signature Purchase Decline (Insufficient Funds [50.0]-Extra Hold Amount (9.296) is required),  DOROS ITALIAN RESTAURA,   ACWORTH, GA, USA
Agent explained the extra hold amount required at eating places. 
Agent should answer what was asked by the CH. 
Agent should have informed the CH that we do not call the CH to inform that the extra hold is put back.
CH called to re-open her card. Agent verified the information mentioned in the card summary and re-opened the card. Agent should use acknowledgment statements.

CH called to file a dispute, Denise’s tone was good, but more empathy statements should’ve been used. The CH was instructed to call back once the transaction is posted to file a dispute for goods/services not received. Account was notated accordingly.

CH called to update his address. Camila’s tone was good, the CH was instructed to send a POA, all pertinent details were provided. Additional assistance was not offered, account was notated accordingly

CH called to inquire about a refund. Lucas did not sound confident during the call and the CH had to explain their issue 3 times. The transaction was for a hotel reservation and was still pending, the path to follow in this scenario is DCFC > CIBC > Pre auth release. No notes found on the account.

Jake’s conversation was fine. CH wanted to know if the card could be reloaded or not and was advised accordingly. CH also wanted to know if the card could be used internationally. Jake first advised the customer that there was no balance on the card to be used and when the CH asked the same question again, Jake advised that if there would have been balance on the card then the customer would have been able to use it, which was an incorrect statement because CH clearly mentioned that he wanted to use the card internationally as he was abroad. This card program of Ready card cannot be used internationally as it is only allowed to be used within US and this is something, which the customer should have been educated about.

CH was very clear stating his concern in the beginning of the call. 
Agent should answer the first question and then ask for next one. 
Hold was for more than 3 minutes without any interaction with CH. 
Agent informed the CH how to check the due date on the App. 
More personalization was required in the call.
Agent should use courtesy and acknowledgement statements. Tone should sound upbeat and energetic. Agent informed CH regarding card renewal. Agent processed money order for CH.
CH called to inquire about the card balance. Agent assisted the Ch with the balance and should work on effective listening.
CH called to inquire about the trans and balance. Agent assisted the CH with his concern. Agent should use courtesy words and acknowledgment statements.

I was able to pull the card account in first attempt. 
CH did not remember the access code, additional authentication was done. 
Card was expired. 
Agent should have used the empathy statement. 
Agent should have first educate the CH what he was going to do before verifying the address. 
Agent later informed the CH that he will send the MO for the remaining funds. 
Time frame should be informed before sending the request.

CH called to inquire about card expiry. Steve’s tone did no sound enthusiastic and there was no acknowledgement of the CH’s concern and no empathy was shown. The CH did not pass authentication, this should’ve been stated clearly on the notes.

CH called to inquire why her outstanding balance was increased from $50 last month to $1600 this month. Agent took a lot of time to understand the Ch’s concern. Agent should have informed the CH that the $1600 was the total outstanding balance but the minimum amount was $32..54, which was eventually told. Agent placed the CH on a hold for more than 4 minutes.

Ch called to check the card balance as she had just received it. Agent informed the Ch that the balance on the card was zero and escalated a request to the back office. Agent should sound helpful and friendly. Agent should use acknowledgment statement.

column11: Failed to file a dispute and/or persuaded the customer from filing
column35: Chris had an okay conversation. CH wanted to know as to why Petal was still showing on his credit report, even though he had canceled his card account on 05/24/2019. Chris advised the customer that it will take 8 weeks for it to stop showing on the credit report, which was not a correct information. It takes upto 8 weeks for Petal to show on the credit report of the customer but the DCFC does not say anything about removing Petal from the credit report. Chris should have taken an ownership to file a credit bureau dispute and then send an escalation to back office to let them know of the customer’s concern.

Agent asked for access code and agent provided address. Agent should have obtained the access code again instead of additional verification as there is a chance that the CH misheard. Agent processed a money order for the CH on his request as the card was about to expire.

Admin was calling to get assistance. 
Agent should have confirmed the phone number given by the CH. 
CH was having 16-20 accounts. 
Agent should have taken the information and escalate it. 
Hold was not required. 
Agent finally took the information and escalated.

Lucas had a fine conversation. CH wanted to know the balance and was assisted accordingly. However, Lucas needs to further advise the customer how they can do the self service and avoid the fee but this was not done on this call. Lucas also needs to listen effectively. On this call, the customer told Lucas that he wanted to check the balance of his wife but Lucas could not understand him. Only after getting the Card ID and accessing the card, Lucas identified that it was someone else’s card and then advised the customer accordingly. If Lucas would have listened carefully and effectively, he would have advised the customer right there (without getting the card ID) that the balance could not be shared without the actual CH being on the phone.

Jennifer’s conversation was fine. Usage of courtesy and empathy words and phrases could have been much better. CH needed assistance with transactions on pre auth with a hotel. There were 3 transactions on hold i.e. $7.60, $148.40, $46.00. CH reported that his actual bill that he owed to the hotel was $157.14 and he was expecting to get his $48 back on the card, which were held as a security hold. CH also reported that he did not want to dispute any of the charges made by them. CH should have been advised to contact the merchant and make them fax all the required information to release the pre auth transaction, which was held as a security but this was not advised to the customer at all. FCR and correct resolution was not ensured on this call.

CH called because her card expired, Sofia’s tone was good but there was no acknowledgement of the issue when the CH first mentioned that her card was expired. The MO was processed after address verification and all the pertinent details were given to the CH. Additional assistance was offered, no notes found on the account.

CH called to reclaim the funds on her expired card, Fabiola’s tone was great but the CH had to repeat her name and address. The MO was processed as requested and the address was verified, instructions on how to redeem the MO, delivery timeframe and check amount were given to the CH. Additional assistance was offered, account was notated accordingly.

Kevin’s conversation was fine. CH reported that she was trying to setup the app on her new android phone but when she was entering her icloud email address, it was not getting accepted. Now this type of caller’s concern falls mainly under the category of either “Technical or Product Troubleshooting” or “Mobile Services” and according to the information, which is mentioned under the highlighted headings of DCFC, an email should have been sent to Petal card but no such escalation was sent and the customer was just advised to send an email to support@petalcard.com, which was not a correct or sufficient information. Also, probing was insufficient and could have been better. “CH called to inform she forgot her password and has no access to icloud account. Assisted” - such notations should be avoided as they do not fully explain about what was advised to the customer. Unannounced pauses must always be avoided and the customer must always be told before they are put on hold.
Steve assisted the CH regarding the funds transfer delay. Account was notated.

Richard’s conversation was just okay. Usage of courtesy, apology, empathy and value added phrases should have been ensured. Richard also needs to ensure not to interrupt the customer while they are speaking but multiple verbal collisions were observed on this call from Richard’s end. CH wanted to get the balance from her card to be cashed out because she did not want to spend the funds down. Richard advised the customer that a money order will be sent to her for the balance available on the card but failed to do so. The card account is still open and active and the funds are still on the card. Moreover, Richard did not take any ownership to verify the address before issuing the money order (which was also not issued in this case). Card account was also not notated.

CH was not able to use the card at Walmart. 
Agent reviewed the account i.e. Pre-Auth Transaction-POS Signature Purchase Decline (Transaction Restricted - Unable to Perform 3-D Secure Authentication),  WALMART.COM,   BENTONVILLE, AR, USA
Agent explained the CH to use the card with Credit option and it should work.
Agent also explained the previous txns with the same merchant. 
There was no decline in Sept.

CH called because she tried to save her payment information for future loads, and it did not work. Denise did not sound friendly, more courtesy phrases should’ve been used. The CH was instructed to try again later, Denise should’ve told them to try a different browser and that they can only load the card twice per day.  Notations were completely different from what happened on the call(\r\nCard activation, after CH ID confirmation).
CH was calling to check the referral points and still waiting for the card. Agent took the information and escalated. 07/29/201916:25:17Web Service - New Card Purchas...New Card Purchase, SGP
